  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citations and public discourse metrics indicating its reach, \"The Hybrid Practitioner,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, reflects a solid engagement with its intended scholarly discourse, particularly in the realm of sustainability.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2022, \"The Hybrid Practitioner\" engages with contemporary issues in scholarly communications, particularly emphasizing intersections between practice and theory in various disciplines. While specific metrics, such as citations and online mentions, remain at zero, the book's relevance is underlined by its strong commercial presence on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, indicating interest among users looking for academic resources.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The examination of inferred roles suggests a notable engagement with policy relevance, as indicated by a connection to one Sustainable Development Goal. This implies that the book may contribute to discussions on aligning hybrid methodologies with sustainable practices, a growing area of interest in many academic and professional fields.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the absence of community discourse on platforms like Wikipedia, Reddit, and Bluesky signifies limited public engagement, the book's positioning within a commercial context suggests it is poised for future discussions as readers interact with its content over time. The lack of scholarly uptake, reflected through citations, shows that while it may currently sit outside prominent academic debates, its foundational ideas may resonate in future research and scholarship.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while \"The Hybrid Practitioner\" shows early indicators of engagement primarily through its commercial linkage, it may yet serve as a catalyst for important conversations in sustainability and hybrid practices as scholars and practitioners continue to explore these themes in greater depth.</p>",
